2.3.5 Using "when" without an argument
	- you can use "when" expression without an argument
		ex)
			========================================
			fun something(a: Int, b: Int) = when {
				a==1 -> "a"
				b==2 -> "b"
				else -> throw Exception()
			}
			========================================
			-> When no argument is supplied for the when expression, the branch condition is any Boolean expression
